TERMS and CONDITIONS The “Demolish the Wowzers Tower” is a limited period contest (“the Contest”) launched by ITC limited (hereinafter referred to as “ITC” or “Company”) Persons participating or seeking to participate in the Contest shall individually be referred to as "Participant" and collectively as "Participants". Please read the terms and conditions (T&Cs) before participating in the contest. Participation in this Contest is purely voluntary. By participating in this Contest, each Participant is deemed to have accepted the complete terms and conditions of this Contest available on www.sunfeastwowzers.com/game (“Contest Website”) as well as the decisions of ITC, which are final and binding in all matters related to the Contest. Successfully entering the Contest and winning a prize is subject to the requirements set forth herein. For the purpose of these T&Cs, wherever the context so requires, “You” or “Your” shall mean any natural person who is participant in the contest and “We” or “Our” shall mean ITC. 1 . Eligibility: (i) This Contest is open to all citizens of India currently residing in India. Participants below the age of 18 can participate only with the consent of their parent(s)/legal guardian. (ii) In addition to the other eligibility criteria contained herein, the Participants (or their legal guardian if they are below the age of 18) should have a government approved photo ID proof, namely, passport, voter card, or driver’s license that is valid during the Contest Period, a copy of which will have to be submitted at the request of ITC, without which the Participants will be disqualified from the Contest. (iii) The following persons are not eligible to participate in the Contest: employees, contractors, directors and officers of ITC, and their subsidiaries and affiliated companies, affiliates, advisors, distributors, Web design, advertising, fulfilment, judging and promotion vendors, involved in the administration, development, fulfilment and execution of this Contest(collectively, “Promotion Parties”) and their immediate family members (spouses, domestic partners, parents, grandparents, siblings, children and grandchildren). (iv) This Contest is open to all the states of India. 2. Contest period: The Contest shall be held from 14 th April 2025 to 31 st May 2025 or any other date as decided by ITC (hereinafter referred to as “ Contest Period ”). 3. How to Participate: To participate in the Contest, a Participant should follow the following steps: (i) The Participants can directly visit the Contest Website www.sunfeastwowzers.com/game and then follow all the steps of participation provided in the microsite. (ii) The link to the Contest will also be posted on the official social media pages of Sunfeast Wowzers in Instagram @sunfeastwowzers and Facebook ‘Sunfeast Wowzers’. (iii) Upon clicking the link, the Participants will be redirected to the official WhatsApp chat bot. Over the WhatsApp chatbot, the Participants will be required to accept these terms and conditions and go through the game rules. Once the terms & conditions are accepted, the Participants will be redirected to the Contest Website. (iv) Participants coming to the microsite directly will have to submit their name, phone number and accept receiving of WhatsApp messages in order to proceed further. (v) The Participant will then have to play the game and stand a chance to win a prize. The game comprises a Wowzers tower. The Participants have to tap the Wowzers tower and demolish the entire tower within the fixed time period in order to complete the game and stand a chance to win a prize. (vi) A participant who demolishes the entire tower, will have their name listed on the leaderboard in the Contest Website. This leaderboard will be updated once every week with the winners for the week. (vii) The participation will be considered valid only if the a) Participant has completed the game by demolishing the tower. b) agrees to the listed terms and conditions. (viii) Participants can have multiple attempts to complete the game throughout the Contest Period. Once the Participant completes the game, they will not be eligible for any further attempts to complete the game. Only one (1) prize per number/person will be permitted. (ix) The name entered by the Participants to enter in to the game cannot be sexually explicit or suggestive, violent or derogatory of any ethnic, racial, gender, religious, professional or age group, profane or pornographic in any manner. Failure to abide by this rule will result in disqualification from the Contest. (x) ITC shall not be responsible for any technical errors. 4 . The Prize (i) For the purpose of the Contest: a) “Prize” shall mean one (1) Amazon gift voucher worth Rs. 100 . b) “Winners” shall mean the Participants who have won the Prize. (ii) Should the Winner be found, in ITC’s sole discretion: not to be eligible to win; not to have complied with these Rules; their conduct can be reasonably interpreted as scamming; acted fraudulently with regards to the Contest; and if it would be unlawful to award the prize, he/she will automatically be disqualified and/or the prize will be forfeited. Winners may also be required to sign acceptance of prizes and indemnity documents. (iii) A Participant, potential prize winner and/or prize winner may, at ITC’s sole discretion, be disqualified from the Contest and/or forfeit his/her prize if: (i) such person’s participation in the Contest and/or the awarding of a prize to such participant would, as solely determined by ITC, be harmful to the goodwill and/or reputation of any of ITC; or (ii) such person engages in any unsafe, illegal, unsociable or inappropriate behavior. (iv) ITC may require each Winner to complete and submit an information disclosure agreement to enable ITC to ensure compliance with these Rules. (v) The prize is not transferable, and no substitution or cash redemption of prize is permitted. A prize will not be handed/awarded to a third party, but only to the verified Winner. (vi) ITC reserves the right, at their sole discretion, to substitute the prize with any other prizes of comparable or greater commercial value for whatever reason. (vii) Prize visuals on any contest and/or promotional materials are for illustrative purposes only 5 . Winner Selection (i) The Participants who completes the game and destroys the tower within the fixed time period will stand a chance to win the Prize. Approximately 10 Participants will be selected at the end of each week based on the leaderboard rankings provided on the Contest Website. This will be depending the number of winners on the website. (ii) This Winner announcement will take place at the end of each week on the leaderboard in the Contest Website. The date of winner announcement is subject to change at the discretion of ITC. The details of Winner will also be declared on official Social Media Pages @sunfeastwowzers on Instagram and Facebook. (iii) At the time that a potential prize winner is identified, the potential prize winner will be contacted by a representative of ITC at which point he/she may be required to answer a few questions regarding his/her eligibility as well as be requested to submit certain documents and a copy of his/her ID and/valid passport or permit and/or driver’s license to ITC’s representative. (iv) The potential prize winner is not an actual winner until his/her participation is validated and his/her documents are completed and submitted to ITC. If a potential prize winner does not meet the eligibility requirements, the prize will be forfeited and a runner up finalist will be deemed the potential prize winner subject to the terms and conditions herein. (v) If ITC are unable to reach any of the potential prize winners after 3 (three) attempts made within 3 (three) working days of their name being drawn, for whatsoever reason, including incorrect telephone numbers or inoperative telephone numbers or delayed responses to social media Private Messages, such winner will be disqualified and a runner up finalist will be deemed the potential prize winner subject to the terms and conditions herein. (vi) Eligible winners will be contacted, electronically by a representative of ITC based on the information they will have shared via the telephone call. (vii) The Winner shall be responsible to comply with the registration process, related formalities and production of any /all such documents/information as may be required by ITC authorities in connection with the Prize. (viii) The decision of ITC will be final and binding with regard to any dispute arising out of this activity. (ix) ITC reserves the sole and absolute right to terminate, modify or extend this Contest, at its absolute discretion without notice and without any liability, without assigning any reason whatsoever. 6 . Other Terms & Conditions: (i) By sharing their personal information with ITC, the Participants consent to collection, storing, processing and use of personal information i.e., (Name, Mobile number) by ITC, its affiliates, associates, agents, contractors and other third parties. (ii) Personal information given by the Participants shall be used to deliver Prizes and for promotional activities by ITC, its affiliates, associates, agents, contractors. (iii) The Participants also have an option to withdraw their consent in relation to usage of personal information during the Contest Period. In such cases, the entry of the Participant shall not be considered, and Participant shall not be eligible for the Prizes. The Participants may reach out to itccares@itc.in or such withdrawals. (iv) By consenting to the Terms and Conditions of this Contest, the Participants acknowledge and consent to transfer and/or disclosure of their personal information by ITC to any third-party. (viii) All material submitted in connection with the Contest (whether written, audio, electronic or visual form, or a combination of those) or any photographs, video and/or film footage and/or audio recording taken of Participants are assigned to ITC upon submission and become the property of ITC exclusively.
